#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:2
msgid "or - conditionally execute a command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:7
msgid "COMMAND1; or COMMAND2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:12
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:14
msgid ""
"``or`` is used to execute a command if the previous command was not "
"successful (returned a status of something other than 0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:16
msgid ""
"``or`` statements may be used as part of the condition in an :doc:`if <if>` "
"or :doc:`while <while>` block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:18
msgid ""
"``or`` does not change the current exit status itself, but the command it "
"runs most likely will. The exit status of the last foreground command to "
"exit can always be accessed using the :ref:`$status <variables-status>` "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:20
msgid "The **-h** or **--help** option displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:23
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:25
msgid ""
"The following code runs the ``make`` command to build a program. If the "
"build succeeds, the program is installed. If either step fails, ``make "
"clean`` is run, which removes the files created by the build process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/or.rst:29
msgid "make; and make install; or make clean"
msgstr ""

